correctness.rationale: The extraction largely conflates multiple experiments and includes many fabricated or schema‑invalid entries. Key issues: (1) Schema violations: processParameters.plasmaPower is set to null while the schema expects an object if present; omit it if not used. (2) Semantic incoherence: A single process lists three different Zn precursors and a long list of substrates; the article treats these as distinct processes/conditions and they should be extracted as separate process instances. (3) Unsupported/fabricated values: pressure (1 mmHg), growth-per-cycle (0.1 Å), number of cycles (100), film thickness (10 nm), purge and co-reactant dosing times (100 ms), flow rates, nucleation period (5 cycles), saturation flag, uniformity (5%), conformality (AR 10), optical properties (n=2.0, absorption coefficient, band gap 3.3 eV), resistivity (1e6 Ω·m), roughness (2 nm), film density (5.6 in GM-PER-DeciM3), XRD/polycrystalline, and XRR/AFM methods are not reported in the article. (4) Internal inconsistency: GPC 0.1 Å × 100 cycles gives ~1 nm, inconsistent with the reported 10 nm film thickness in thicknessControl and processParameters. (5) Unit error: carrier density is given as 1e17 with unit PER-M3, but the article reports ~1e17 cm^-3; correct value in SI would be ~1e23 m^-3. (6) DeviceProperties misuse: threshold voltage, subthreshold swing, and device structure (bottom-gate top-contact) are TFT metrics not discussed in the paper; on/off ratio 1e5 is for Schottky/p–n junctions and is misplaced under TFT deviceProperties. (7) Missing/omitted but available details: DEZn pulse lengths (90/60/40 ms) and temperature ranges (90–140 °C and 100 °C case) are partially captured (only 90 ms used), while the co-reactant variant (H2O+NH4OH for N-doping) is not represented. To correct: split into separate processes per precursor/substrate/condition; remove null plasmaPower; restrict to values explicitly stated; fix carrier density units; resolve GPC/thickness consistency; drop unsupported optical/flow/pressure/uniformity/conformality/roughness/density/TFT fields or provide traceable values.

completeness.rationale: The extraction is largely non-traceable and conflates multiple experiments into a single, incoherent process. Major issues: (1) Multiple processes in the article are not represented separately: zinc acetate at ~280 C, DEZn/DMZn low-temperature (90–140 C) processes with varying DEZn pulse lengths (90, 60, 40 ms), and the N-doped process using a water+ammonia (NH4OH) co-reactant followed by RTP anneal at 400 C for 30 min to achieve p-type and p–n junctions. The extraction provides only one generic TALD ZnO process and merges substrates and conditions across experiments. (2) Many parameters are fabricated and not reported in the article, violating traceability and schema-guided extraction: reactor details, pressure, flow rates, purge times (except DEZn pulse length), growth-per-cycle, number of cycles, film thickness, saturation, nucleation period, uniformity, conformality, refractive index, absorption coefficient, band gap method, elemental concentrations and atomic ratio, roughness, film density, and TFT device metrics. (3) Misuse/mismatch of schema/device context: deviceProperties pertains to TFTs, but the article reports Schottky and p–n diode characteristics (e.g., rectifying ratio 1e4–1e7), not TFT parameters; the extracted TFT metrics are invented. (4) Unit/quantity errors: carrier density is given as 1e17 m^-3, whereas the article reports ~1e17 cm^-3 (≈1e23 m^-3); resistivity not reported; film density unit/value is inconsistent (5.6 g/dm^3). (5) Schema issues: plasmaPower is set to null despite being an object type; substrate is a single string listing many distinct substrates, reducing semantic coherence. Required additions/revisions: split into distinct processes (DEZn LT at 90–100 C with specific DEZn pulse lengths; DMZn LT; zinc acetate at ~280 C; N-doped with NH4OH co-reactant and RTP anneal), include ammonia co-reactant for the p-type process, report only dosing time(s) actually given (e.g., DEZn 90/60/40 ms) and remove unreported parameters (or leave fields absent if optional), correct carrier density units/magnitudes, include Schottky/p–n diode rectifying ratios in an appropriate field (not TFT deviceProperties), and remove null/object mismatches.
